place.name: RUNCTON HOLME
place.gazetteerText: HOLME-NEXT-RUNCTON, a parish in Downham district, Norfolk; adjacent to the Ely and Lynn railway, and near the river Ouse, 1½ mile SSE of Watlington r. station, and 4¼ N by E of Downham-Market. Posttown, Watlington, under Downham. Acres, 1, 096. Real property, £1, 884. Pop., 273. Houses, 56. The manor belongs to Mr. Cox. The living is a rectory, annexed to the rectory of South Runcton, in the diocese of Norwich. The church has a tower, and a memorial window. There are a national school, and charities £20. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
